Description:
A NYC state of style & sophistication
Resonating with an irresistible New York narrative of style and sophistication, this brilliant warehouse apartment spectacularly unfolds from vast sky-lit entry to beautifully renovated interior in a buzzing lifestyle locale. Secured towards the rear of a coveted Foy & Gibson complex including basement car space on title; enjoy 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom multi-level living then step out onto the street and be immersed in an exciting mix of cafes, restaurants, bars, galleries and boutiques. Superbly integrating strong heritage character in a sublime contemporary context, this one-owner home includes main bedroom with ensuite, study nook, high-ceiling living and dining, stunning new Caesarstone concrete kitchen, laundry, original exposed beams, new carpet and polished hardwood floors, plus ample storage.
Insights: 13/76 Oxford Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Classic Victorian appeal, spacious and renovated with flair
In one of Collingwood's premier streets, this immaculately renovated and extended residence with classic period detail offers spacious light-filled living, comprising three generous double bedrooms (BIRs: upper-level main with ensuite & CBD views); a well-equipped kitchen opening to a spacious living/dining room and ROW-access, entertaining courtyard with off-street parking; stylish second bathroom & euro laundry. Including a light court, this inviting home, close to Victoria Park station and neighbourhood cafes, walk to Smith and Brunswick Streets, features Baltic floors, period detail, hydronic heating, split-system air conditioning and large loft storage. Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Period grace with contemporary architectural flair
OPEN FOR INSPECTION CANCELLED 18/11/17
Characterised by its timeless period attributes and stunning renovations, this Victorian showpiece delivers a lifestyle of absolute quality, versatility and city-edge practicality.
- Large west facing front bedroom branches off the classic hallway
- Beautiful second bedroom with built-in robes and study nook
- A lounge room invites relaxation and features split system air conditioning/heating, Yamaha surround sound system and stunning polished floorboards
- The new galley style kitchen with an abundance of storage,features a pantry, a Smeg oven and a dishwasher
- The new bathroom to the rear with Euro laundry
- A stylish deck and landscaped courtyard with a Kumquat tree promises alfresco enjoyment
- Currently 2 parking permits for street parking, timber floors, high ceilings and stunning period traits
Just a short stroll to Gertrude and Smith Street, Victoria Streets cafes, restaurants, shopping and transport plus East Melbourne Parks/Gardens and MCG close by.

Description:
Classy conversion with amazing space
Melbourne meets Manhattan in Collingwood's iconic Foy & Gibson precinct with this sensational upstairs apartment boasting an expansive floorplan, towering ceilings throughout and a vivid mix of industrial edge and contemporary cool. Light-filled interior showcases 2 double bedrooms (both with robes), ensuite and main bathroom, vast open-plan living and dining spaces complemented by a stone-bench kitchen with stainless steel appliances and ample cupboard space. Add to this a private terrace, gas heating, European laundry, polished floorboards, exposed brickwork and pillars, plus secure foyer and undercover parking space. An exceptional inner-city lifestyle/investment opportunity; Smith Street cafes and restaurants, shops and supermarkets, city-bound trams are all within easy reach.

Description:
STYLISH & CONTEMPORARY WAREHOUSE APARTMENT OOZING NEW YORK FLAVOURS
Nestled in the heritage Foy & Gibson Woollen Mills warehouse, this remarkably elegant and secure inner urban domain is one of few remaining in Collingwood.
A modern and working kitchen features SMEG appliances and flows through to the open and airy dining and living space. Polished concrete floors open out onto a fabulous private terrace bathed in natural light, ideal for entertaining or a weekend breakfast in the sun.
Two ample, carpeted bedrooms include BIR's and wall heaters, with the master opening to the terrace. These are separated by a central bathroom and a European laundry with plenty of storage.
Factor in high ceilings, reverse cycle AC, secure entrance with video intercom, secure lower level carpark and a storage cage and the property's appeal deepens.
Enhancing this further is its superb location; a stone’s throw from Smith Street bustling cafes, restaurants and shopping precinct, with trams, buses and trains nearby to access the heart of Melbourne City and the Sporting precinct.
Conditions of entry – IDENTIFICATION and contact number required, otherwise entry may be refused.

Description:
Collingwood Investor Choice - Yorkshire Brewery
Investor Choice - Securely Leased!
The nostalgic feel of yester-year is beautifully preserved in this impressive one year old modern apartment. Enjoy modern living in this impressive city fringe one bedroom apartment. Situated in the new Yorkshire Brewery of Collingwood, this stunning home with northerly aspect views and an abundance of natural light is the natural choice for the buyer looking for a new place to call home.
The apartment comprises a spacious bedroom with built in wardrobe, study nook and window, a galley kitchen with quality European appliances, gas cook-top, dishwasher, refrigerator, and generous cupboard space, open plan living room with northerly aspect views opening onto private balcony, a practical bathroom with shower and vanity as well as a separate laundry facility. The home is bright and cosy with the added comfort of classic timber flooring that flows through the property.
Residents enjoy the convenience of an onsite building manager, rooftop lounge with BBQ area, gymnasium and library, plus a roof top private kitchen and dining room to host your private dinner party. Park your car in the secure car park and skip hop and jump to the Smith Street cafes, Brunswick Street shops, tram to the city and universities, or simple wander along and enjoy the surrounding neighbourhood attractions.
If you are looking for places to buy in Collingwood then you really should inspect this home. Apartments for sale in Collingwood do not get any better than this. Invest now and occupy in the long term.
The property is securely LEASED! Inspection by appointment with Chris Snell on 0418 328 961

Description:
Smith & Co. Lifestyle With Spectacular Views
Perched high above the fervour of popular Smith Street and part of the sleek and recently built Smith & Co. development, this sub-penthouse apartment presents the highest standard in contemporary living, with quality fixtures and fittings throughout. Boasting exceptional, uninterrupted city skyline and edgy urban views, the light-filled and expansive interior (85 m2 approx.) comprises 2 generously proportioned bedrooms with BIRs (main with ensuite), spacious open plan living with designer kitchen servicing the dining and living zones that open onto the enormous terrace (85 m2 approx.) that envelops the entire apartment and ideal for roof top entertaining. With gleaming bathrooms, Euro laundry, optimally glazed windows, heating and cooling, secure intercom entry, basement OSP (with storage cage) and lift access to Smith Street. Stylish communal areas of the development include several gardens with covered BBQ areas, rooftop terraces and library lounge. Enjoy an incomparable inner-northern lifestyle as you step out your door to all the artisanal shops, trams, cafes, fine dining and nightlife that Smith, Gertrude and Brunswick Street are renowned for, and all the side-street favourites Collingwood has to offer.

Description:
Big, bold and boutique
Situated in Collingwood's iconic Foy & Gibson precinct, this two-level Powerhouse apartment is set to impress with its grand proportions, first-class features and blissfully secure surrounds. High ceilings throughout emphasizing the home's oversized dimensions, the apartment's impeccable interior boasts 2 bedrooms (both with robes) and study/home office, deluxe modern ensuite and main bathroom, vast open-plan living/dining area leading out to a full-width undercover terrace. Add to this a granite-top kitchen with Miele appliances and ample cupboard space, heating and cooling, new carpets, laundry/powder room (third WC), plus lift to secure foyer and undercover parking space. Stroll to Smith Street's cool cafes and renowned restaurants, shops and supermarkets, trams to the CBD.
Insights: 27/99 Oxford Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Rare double-block seclusion with space & flexibility
Stake a significant city-edge claim with a rare double-block discovery on the corner of Gold and Easey Streets in Collingwood. This light-filled 7-room Victorian delivers flexible modern space for a range of lifestyle scenarios. The large proportioned, single-level warehouse-like setting provides infinite inspiration for families, professionals, creatives or downsizers to live, work and play. It is well located near all the attractions of Smith and Brunswick Streets, parkland, trams and train station. This secluded home includes 4 sizable bedrooms, study, open-plan living and dining zone adjoining sun-drenched courtyard garden, versatile lounge room, bright kitchen, 2 bathrooms and laundry, gas log heater, Victorian Ash and Jarrah floorboards, and new carpets.
Insights: 33-35 Gold Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 3 other 4 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Authentic period character, convenient CBD-edge address
This wide 1880s terrace is a home of special warmth and charm, well-located close to neighbourhood cafes and within walking distance to the CBD, Smith Street and the Convent Arts precinct. Set behind a walled garden, it offers a versatile floor plan comprising a large sitting room/3rd BR and living room opening to light court; 2 further upper-level bedrooms, a retreat with custom BIRs, plus study zone; country-style timber kitchen and glass-ceilinged bathroom/laundry. Including a secluded courtyard garden with storage and ROW-access off street parking, this light-filled residence features ample roof storage, patinated Baltic floors, deep cornices, working OFPs, gas log fire, solar panels and security system.
Insights: 21 Vere Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 24 other 3 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
PERIOD PRIZE WITH DUAL STREET ACCESS!
Positioned to perfection with the best of Collingwood and Fitzroy in easy reach, this Federation gem delivers a lifestyle of immediate quality and class along with value-adding options to further enhance and expand (STCA). Beyond its gorgeous facade, the home's inviting interior comprises two genuinely large bedrooms, bathroom and separate WC, open lounge/dining area enhanced by a light-filled kitchen with timber benchtops, dishwasher and ample cupboard space. Add to this two gas-coal fireplaces, alarm system, high ceilings, internal laundry facilities, plus a brick-paved rear courtyard complete with off-street parking space (remote-controlled rollerdoor to Little Wellington Street). Enviably located, it's walking distance to Smith Street's cool cafes and renowned restaurants, boutique shops and major supermarkets, as well as trams to the CBD.
Insights: 35 Otter Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 29 other 2 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.
